                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract1296-1">Jacob "the cut-up" was a noble Persian from
          the Royal City of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/35">Beth Lapaṭ</placeName>. He
          became a Christian, but he later abjured his Christian identity. His family reproached
          him, so he confessed his faith before Bahram V and was martyred.</note>
